<section id="malware" class="card">
  <span class="kicker">Malware Types</span>
  <h2>Malware Types</h2>
  <div style="display:grid; gap:18px; grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr));">

    <div class="card">
      <h3>üìõ Virus</h3>
      <p>
        Attaches to legitimate files and spreads when executed.<br>
        <strong>Effect:</strong> Corrupts or deletes data.<br>
        <strong>Protect Yourself:</strong> Use antivirus software and avoid opening unknown email attachments.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>ü™± Worm</h3>
      <p>
        Spreads across networks without user action.<br>
        <strong>Effect:</strong> Slows systems, spreads fast.<br>
        <strong>Protect Yourself:</strong> Keep your operating system and software updated, and use a firewall.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>üß® Ransomware</h3>
      <p>
        Encrypts files and demands payment.<br>
        <strong>Effect:</strong> Locks users out of their data.<br>
        <strong>Protect Yourself:</strong> Back up your data regularly and avoid clicking on suspicious links.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>üïµÔ∏è Spyware</h3>
      <p>
        Monitors user activity secretly.<br>
        <strong>Effect:</strong> Captures passwords, keystrokes.<br>
        <strong>Protect Yourself:</strong> Use anti-spyware tools and avoid installing shady browser extensions.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>üé≠ Trojan</h3>
      <p>
        Disguised as legit software.<br>
        <strong>Effect:</strong> Installs other malware, steals data.<br>
        <strong>Protect Yourself:</strong> Download software only from official or trusted sources.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>üì¢ Adware</h3>
      <p>
        Shows unwanted ads.<br>
        <strong>Effect:</strong> Slows system, annoying popups.<br>
        <strong>Protect Yourself:</strong> Avoid free software bundles and use an ad blocker.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>üõ†Ô∏è Rootkit</h3>
      <p>
        Grants stealth admin access.<br>
        <strong>Effect:</strong> Hides other malware.<br>
        <strong>Protect Yourself:</strong> Keep your system updated and use security software with rootkit detection.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>‚å®Ô∏è Keylogger</h3>
      <p>
        Records every keystroke.<br>
        <strong>Effect:</strong> Steals login credentials.<br>
        <strong>Protect Yourself:</strong> Use anti-keylogger software and enable 2FA on accounts.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>ü§ñ Botnet</h3>
      <p>
        Network of controlled devices.<br>
        <strong>Effect:</strong> Launches attacks like DDoS.<br>
        <strong>Protect Yourself:</strong> Keep your router firmware updated and avoid unsecured IoT devices.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>üß¨ Fileless Malware</h3>
      <p>
        Lives in memory, uses legit tools.<br>
        <strong>Effect:</strong> Hard to detect or remove.<br>
        <strong>Protect Yourself:</strong> Use behavioral-based antivirus tools and restrict admin rights.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Additional Virus Types -->

    <div class="card">
      <h3>üóÇÔ∏è File Infector Virus</h3>
      <p>
        Infects executable files (.exe, .com).<br>
        <strong>Effect:</strong> Spreads when infected files run.<br>
        <strong>Protect Yourself:</strong> Avoid running unknown files and scan downloads.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>üíΩ Boot Sector Virus</h3>
      <p>
        Infects the boot sector or master boot record.<br>
        <strong>Effect:</strong> Activates before OS boots.<br>
        <strong>Protect Yourself:</strong> Use updated antivirus and avoid using untrusted external drives.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>üìÑ Macro Virus</h3>
      <p>
        Targets macros in documents like Word or Excel.<br>
        <strong>Effect:</strong> Spreads via infected documents.<br>
        <strong>Protect Yourself:</strong> Disable macros and scan attachments before opening.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>üîÑ Polymorphic Virus</h3>
      <p>
        Changes its code to avoid detection.<br>
        <strong>Effect:</strong> Hard to detect with signature-based antivirus.<br>
        <strong>Protect Yourself:</strong> Use heuristic and behavior-based antivirus tools.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>üîß Metamorphic Virus</h3>
      <p>
        Rewrites its own code before infecting.<br>
        <strong>Effect:</strong> Evades detection by changing structure.<br>
        <strong>Protect Yourself:</strong> Keep software updated and use advanced antivirus.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>üß† Resident Virus</h3>
      <p>
        Stays in memory to infect files during use.<br>
        <strong>Effect:</strong> Infects files dynamically.<br>
        <strong>Protect Yourself:</strong> Use real-time antivirus protection.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>‚ö° Direct Action Virus</h3>
      <p>
        Infects files only when executed, doesn‚Äôt stay in memory.<br>
        <strong>Effect:</strong> Quick infection upon execution.<br>
        <strong>Protect Yourself:</strong> Scan files before execution.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>‚ôæÔ∏è Multipartite Virus</h3>
      <p>
        Infects boot sector and executable files simultaneously.<br>
        <strong>Effect:</strong> Multiple infection points make it hard to remove.<br>
        <strong>Protect Yourself:</strong> Use full system scans and boot sector protection.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>üïµÔ∏è‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏è Stealth Virus</h3>
      <p>
        Hides itself by intercepting system requests.<br>
        <strong>Effect:</strong> Difficult to detect.<br>
        <strong>Protect Yourself:</strong> Use heuristic antivirus and behavioral analysis.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>üîí Encrypted Virus</h3>
      <p>
        Encrypts its code to hide from antivirus.<br>
        <strong>Effect:</strong> Activates only after decryption.<br>
        <strong>Protect Yourself:</strong> Use antivirus with encryption detection.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>üï≥Ô∏è Spacefiller (Cavity) Virus</h3>
      <p>
        Inserts itself into empty spaces in files.<br>
        <strong>Effect:</strong> Avoids increasing file size, harder to detect.<br>
        <strong>Protect Yourself:</strong> Use deep scanning antivirus tools.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>üìÑ Companion Virus</h3>
      <p>
        Creates new files with similar names to run first.<br>
        <strong>Effect:</strong> Tricks OS into executing the virus.<br>
        <strong>Protect Yourself:</strong> Monitor file extensions and suspicious files.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>‚ùå Overwrite Virus</h3>
      <p>
        Overwrites and destroys original file content.<br>
        <strong>Effect:</strong> Causes data loss.<br>
        <strong>Protect Yourself:</strong> Keep backups and avoid suspicious files.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>üåê Browser Hijacker Virus</h3>
      <p>
        Alters browser settings or redirects traffic.<br>
        <strong>Effect:</strong> Changes homepage, inserts ads.<br>
        <strong>Protect Yourself:</strong> Avoid unknown extensions and reset browser settings.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>üìß Email Virus</h3>
      <p>
        Spreads through infected email attachments.<br>
        <strong>Effect:</strong> Infects systems via emails.<br>
        <strong>Protect Yourself:</strong> Don‚Äôt open suspicious attachments and use email filters.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>üåê Network Virus</h3>
      <p>
        Spreads over networks exploiting vulnerabilities.<br>
        <strong>Effect:</strong> Infects multiple systems.<br>
        <strong>Protect Yourself:</strong> Use firewalls and patch systems regularly.
      </p>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

