<section id="help" role="region" aria-labelledby="help-title">
  <span class="kicker">If You‚Äôre Hacked</span>

  <h2 id="help-title">Steps to Take if You‚Äôre Hacked</h2>

  <ol class="tips">
    <li tabindex="0">
      <strong>Change Important Passwords:</strong> Start with email, banking, and social media accounts to prevent further access.
      <div class="backup">If you can‚Äôt change passwords immediately, enable account recovery options or use temporary lock features.</div>
    </li>
    <li tabindex="0">
      <strong>Enable Two-Factor Authentication (2FA):</strong> If you haven‚Äôt already, turn it on immediately for extra security.
      <div class="backup">If 2FA isn‚Äôt available, consider security questions, backup email, or phone number verification.</div>
    </li>
    <li tabindex="0">
      <strong>Run a Malware Scan:</strong> Use trusted antivirus or anti-malware tools to detect and remove threats.
      <div class="backup">If you don‚Äôt have antivirus installed, use reputable online scanners or safe mode scans.</div>
    </li>
    <li tabindex="0">
      <strong>Warn Your Contacts:</strong> Notify friends, family, or colleagues if your account was compromised to prevent spreading scams.
      <div class="backup">If you can‚Äôt access your contacts, post a public warning on your social media profiles or notify through mutual contacts.</div>
    </li>
    <li tabindex="0">
      <strong>Report & Notify:</strong> Inform the affected service providers and, if necessary, relevant authorities about the breach.
      <div class="backup">If you can‚Äôt reach service providers immediately, document all suspicious activity and report as soon as possible.</div>
    </li>
  </ol>
</section>

